      "created": "2026-03-24T10:25:33.958Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "incubating",
      "title": "hordestack: lightweight libvirt-backed bare metal VM + K8s provider for HORDE",
      "description": "New backend provider built on libvirt with minimal VM and K8s CRUD API. CloudStack replacement targeting bare metal without heavy cloud machinery. Feature branch: feat/hordestack-provider. GitHub issue: https://github.com/NVIDIA-dev/horde/issues/5",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-24T10:29:08.301Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: project: null \u2192 \"NVIDIA-dev/horde\"; repo: null \u2192 \"NVIDIA-dev/horde\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-24T10:29:16.322Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "comment",
          "text": "review: solid foundation. One required fix before PR: GPU PCI address parsing in utils.py has an off-by-one risk for addresses without domain prefix (01:00.0 vs 0000:01:00.0). Recommend regex parse + edge case test. Everything else (asyncio wrapping, graceful stop, error handling, 12 tests) is clean. Follow-up issues: overlay_path hardcoded, no connection pooling, os.remove unguarded, x86_64 arch hardcoded. Ready to merge after PCI fix."
        }
