      "id": "wq-API-1774487288554",
      "itemVersion": 1,
      "created": "2026-03-26T01:08:08.554Z",
      "source": "natasha:idea",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "incubating",
      "title": "CCC heartbeat liveness monitor: alert when agent goes silent >30min during business hours",
      "description": "Currently the CCC dashboard shows last heartbeat timestamp, but no alert fires when an agent stops posting heartbeats. A lightweight liveness check in the CCC API (or a cron job on Rocky) should detect agents that have not posted a heartbeat in >30min during 08:00-22:00 PT and fire a Mattermost/Slack alert to jkh. Prevents silent agent death going unnoticed. Grounded in: the Boris silence incident (wq-R-018) where a 3h gap required manual investigation. Heartbeat data is already in /api/heartbeats \u2014 this is purely a threshold check + notification layer.",
      "notes": "",
