      "id": "wq-API-1774728177052",
      "itemVersion": 6,
      "created": "2026-03-28T20:02:57.052Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "pending",
      "title": "WASM UI: Final cutover \u2014 retire legacy Node dashboards, move to port 8789",
      "description": "GATE: wasm-ui-5 (tests) must be 100% passing and reviewed by Natasha + Bullwinkle before this task starts.\nSteps:\n1. Stop legacy Node dashboard (pid on port 8788, ~/.rcc/workspace/dashboard/server.mjs)\n2. Stop legacy clawchat Node server (port 8790, ~/.rcc/workspace/clawchat/server.mjs)\n3. Move dashboard-server to port 8789 (was CCC internal port \u2014 CCC moves to 18789 or similar, dashboard-server becomes the public face)\n   OR: keep CCC on 8789, move dashboard to 80/443 behind nginx\n   Decision needed from jkh before executing.\n4. Update all agent configs that reference old ports\n5. Create systemd unit for dashboard-server so it survives reboots\n6. Archive (don't delete) the legacy Node code to ~/.rcc/workspace/legacy-archive/\n7. Update MEMORY.md and ARCHITECTURE.md to reflect new topology\n8. Notify jkh + crew that cutover is complete",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T20:21:06.271Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "comment",
          "text": "Blocked pending jkh port layout decision: keep CCC on 8789 + move dashboard to 80/443 behind nginx, OR move CCC to 18789 and dashboard-server becomes public face on 8789. Also: wasm-ui-5 tests must be 100% passing first. Not starting cutover until both gates clear."
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T20:52:16.970Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "comment",
          "text": "Rocky checked 2026-03-28 13:51 PT: WASM dashboard is live on port 8790. Gate requires: (1) wasm-ui-5 tests 100% passing + Natasha+Bullwinkle sign-off, (2) jkh decision on port topology (keep CCC on 8789 and move dashboard to 80/443 behind nginx, OR reassign ports). Blocked pending both. Flagging for jkh."
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T21:08:18.884Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T21:08:35.185Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "comment",
          "text": "Natasha review 2026-03-28T21:07 PT: Both gates still unresolved. (1) jkh port decision needed (CCC stays on 8789 + nginx for dashboard, or ports shift). (2) wasm-ui-5 tests confirmed 18/18 passing on sparky aarch64 (commit 053c166) \u2014 Natasha sign-off \u2705. Need Bullwinkle sign-off and jkh port decision before cutover executes. Releasing claim \u2014 will re-claim when unblocked."
        },
