      "id": "RENDER-002",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-21T16:01:07.556Z",
      "source": "natasha",
      "assignee": "boris",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Render: Taiwan Street Scene Animation",
      "description": "GPU render job routed from Natasha to Boris (dual L40 Sweden). See ClawBus seq 28 for job details.",
      "notes": "Natasha routed via ClawBus. Boris has 2x L40 \u2014 primary render target per wq-B-009.",
      "tags": [
        "render",
        "gpu",
        "boris",
        "omniverse"
      ],
      "votes": [
        "natasha"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "boris",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-22T04:01:28Z",
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-22T05:05:00Z",
      "result": null,
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-22T03:32:25.541Z",
          "author": "jkh",
          "type": "ai",
          "text": "\u2728 what is blocked here"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-22T03:32:51.986Z",
          "author": "\ud83d\udc3f\ufe0f Rocky",
          "type": "ai",
          "text": "Let me pull the actual ClawBus queue to see what's in seq 28 and what the current state is.\n\nHere's what's blocked on **RENDER-002 (Taiwan Street Scene Animation)**:\n\n**Status: `pending` \u2014 Boris has never claimed it.**\n\nLooking at the data:\n\n- **Seq 28** (2026-03-21T10:25 UTC): Natasha sent the job spec to Boris via ClawBus \u2705\n- **Seq 40** (2026-03-21T16:01 UTC): Rocky explicitly pinged Boris about both render jobs \u2705\n- **Seq 38** (Boris's response): Boris said he set up heartbeat + poll crons, created the formal queue items... but **never actually claimed RENDER-002** \u274c\n- Every Boris cycle since (cycles 3\u201310, 19:00 UTC yesterday through 03:00 UTC today): all report **\"0 pending items\"** \u2014 meaning Boris's local queue either never received RENDER-002, or his cron is filtering it out\n\n**Root cause:** Boris self-reports 0 pending items every cycle, but RENDER-002 is sitting `pending` with `claimedBy: null` in the dashboard. His poll cron (`boris-clawbus-poll`) apparently isn't translating bus messages into workqueue claims properly \u2014 or his local `queue.json` isn't syncing with the dashboard's queue.\n\n**Also blocked:** `wq-R-016` (Boris health heartbeat to MinIO) is still `pending` \u2014 Boris said he completed it (seq 38), but it's not marked done in the queue.\n\n**Same pattern for RENDER-001** (HORDE Factory Floor), which is also `pending`/unclaimed.\n\nBoth renders are effectively stuck waiting for Boris to actually claim them. Want me to ping Boris directly on the bus to investigate?"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-22T03:33:15.154Z",
          "author": "jkh",
          "type": "comment",
          "text": "yes"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-22T04:01:28.362Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"boris\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-22T04:01:28Z\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-22T04:40:36.787Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; completedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-22T05:05:00Z\""
        }
      ]
    },
