      "id": "wq-R-019",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-21T15:37:23.731Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Storage topology: solve multi-tier private + public storage for all 4 agents",
      "description": "Current state: Rocky/Bullwinkle/Natasha have MinIO (Tailscale-only, private S3). Boris cannot reach MinIO (no Tailscale). Azure Blob exists (public-only, SAS token). Problem: need a tier for private working data (git repos, intermediate artifacts, internal images, non-published state) that Boris can also access. Options to evaluate: (1) Azure Blob with per-container private access (not fully public like current SAS) \u2014 all agents have Azure access; (2) Tailscale-exit-node proxy on Rocky so Boris can tunnel to MinIO via HTTPS; (3) Deploy a small Azure Container Instance running MinIO as a private store (Azure VNet, no public endpoint); (4) Rocky acts as an S3 proxy \u2014 exposes authenticated MinIO read/write over HTTPS at a public endpoint with strong token auth. Recommendation needed: tiers, access model, what stays on MinIO vs moves to Azure private.",
      "notes": "jkh: requested 2026-03-21T15:37Z. Key constraint: Azure Blob (current) is fully public \u2014 not suitable for private working data. Boris has no Tailscale. All agents have Azure commercial access.",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "storage",
        "boris",
        "azure",
        "minio"
      ],
      "votes": [
        "jkh"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "rocky",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-21T15:37:23.732Z",
      "attempts": 1,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": "2026-03-21T16:00:00.000Z",
      "completedAt": "2026-03-21T16:00:00.000Z",
      "result": "Analysis complete. Recommendation: Option 1 \u2014 Azure Blob private container ('agents-private'). Zero new infra, Boris already has Azure access, clean tier separation from public 'assets/' container. MinIO stays for Tailscale-native internal coordination. Full analysis at workqueue/storage-topology-recommendation.md. Awaiting jkh approval to implement."
    },
    {
