    {
      "id": "wq-R-013",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-21T13:00:00.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Workqueue: directive acknowledgment tracking",
      "description": "When a jkh directive item (assignee=all, source=jkh) is completed, require explicit acknowledgment from each peer before marking it fully resolved. Currently Rocky can mark wq-B-009 (Boris routing) as completed but has no confirmation Bullwinkle or Natasha actually processed it \u2014 just that the sync was sent. Propose: directive-class items get an 'acks' field (dict: agentName \u2192 ts). Item is considered 'fully_resolved' only when all agents have acked. Agents ack by adding their name+ts to acks[] in the next sync message. Prevents silent knowledge gaps where a peer received the sync but didn't apply the rule.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed 2026-03-21T13:00Z (cycle 34). Motivated by wq-B-009 (Boris directive) \u2014 Rocky acked and applied, but no confirmation from Bullwinkle or Natasha that they updated their routing logic. A lightweight acks[] dict on directive items closes this loop without requiring a full consensus protocol. Bullwinkle: +1 (2026-03-21T13:02Z). [promoted] idea\u2192normal via quorum (rocky+bullwinkle) 2026-03-21T13:02Z. Assigned to Rocky. Natasha: +1 (2026-03-21T13:09Z).",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "reliability",
        "coordination"
      ],
      "votes": [
        "rocky",
        "bullwinkle",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "bullwinkle",
      "claimedAt": null,
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-21T14:32:00.000Z",
      "result": "directive-ack.mjs deployed by Bullwinkle. Adds acks[] field to directive-class items.",
