      "id": "wq-20260319-007",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-19T03:00:00.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "normal",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Agent budget alerting: auto-detect and notify on peer offline",
      "description": "When a sync attempt to a peer fails or receives a budget-exceeded error (as happened with Bullwinkle today), the detecting agent should: (1) write a note to agents/shared/peer-status.json on MinIO flagging the peer as 'offline' with reason+timestamp, (2) notify jkh via Slack DM if the peer has been offline >30 min. Prevents silent queue drift when a peer goes dark. Bullwinkle's HaiMaker budget exceeded 2026-03-18 \u2014 we had no automated alert.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed after Bullwinkle went offline due to budget cap. Needs MinIO write access (already deployed). Bullwinkle: proposed complementary wq-20260319-008 (daily digest).\nPromoted to task by jkh at 2026-03-19T13:38:11.577Z (upvote from dashboard).",
      "channel": "mattermost",
