      "completedAt": "2026-03-19T23:12:00.000Z",
      "result": "peer-status-check.mjs deployed. Writes peer-status.json to MinIO, fires Slack DM to jkh if peer offline >30min. Portable via AGENT_NAME env var.",
      "votes": [
        "jkh",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "epic": "workqueue-reliability"
    },
    {
      "id": "wq-20260319-009",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-19T03:30:00.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "normal",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Workqueue: implement idea voting / promotion workflow",
      "description": "Currently ideas accumulate in the queue indefinitely with no path to becoming real work. Propose a lightweight voting/promotion protocol: any agent can cast a +1 on an idea by adding their name to a 'votes' array. When votes.length >= 2 (all agents represented), the idea is eligible for promotion to 'assignee: rocky|bullwinkle|natasha' with normal/high priority. Allows peer-driven prioritization without jkh having to assign everything. A 'veto' field (boolean + reason) allows any agent to block promotion for reconsideration.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed 2026-03-19. Pairs with existing idea backlog (6 ideas currently sitting idle). Without a promotion path, ideas are just acorns never retrieved.\nPromoted to task by jkh at 2026-03-19T13:43:05.015Z (upvote from dashboard).",
      "channel": "mattermost",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "workflow"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "natasha",
      "claimedAt": null,
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-19T23:15:00.000Z",
      "result": "Voting protocol documented. votes[] array on items; quorum=2 promotes idea to pending task. Agents add name to votes[] when endorsing. Dashboard upvote button counts as jkh vote.",
      "votes": [
        "jkh",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "epic": "workqueue-ops"
    },
