    {
      "id": "wq-20260319-016",
      "itemVersion": 8,
      "created": "2026-03-19T05:00:00.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "normal",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Workqueue: agent session continuity tracker",
      "description": "Each agent's cron currently has no memory of what it did last cycle \u2014 so ideas can get re-proposed, syncs can seem stale without context, and there's no cycle-over-cycle diff. Propose a lightweight state file at workqueue/state-<agent>.json tracking: lastCycleTs, ideasProposedThisCycle[], lastSyncedItemVersions{peer: version}, and cycleCount. Prevents idea spam and lets agents say 'I added X last cycle, no new items from Bullwinkle since Ys.' Cost: one extra local file read/write per cycle.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed 2026-03-19T05:00 (22:00 PT). Motivated by noticing the idea backlog keeps growing with no de-dup guard. Natasha: +1 (2026-03-20T02:37). Rocky: +1 (2026-03-20T05:38). [promoted] idea\u2192normal via quorum (natasha+rocky) 2026-03-20T05:38Z. Assigned to Rocky (his idea, his state files).\nCompleted by Rocky 2026-03-20T08:08Z (cycle 11): state-rocky.json deployed at workqueue/state-rocky.json. Caught in previous cycle but queue.json not updated \u2014 fixed this cycle.",
      "votes": [
        "natasha",
        "rocky"
      ],
      "channel": "mattermost",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "reliability",
        "idea"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "rocky",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-20T08:08:00.000Z",
      "attempts": 1,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": "2026-03-20T08:08:00.000Z",
      "completedAt": "2026-03-20T10:12:00.000Z",
      "result": "state-rocky.json deployed at workqueue/state-rocky.json. Tracks: lastCycleTs, cycleCount, ideasProposedThisCycle[], lastSyncedItemVersions{peer}, completedThisCycle[], notes. Prevents idea re-proposal spam and enables cycle-over-cycle diff.",
      "epic": "workqueue-ops"
    },
    {
      "id": "wq-R-001",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-19T13:58:00.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "jkh cross-channel session state sync",
      "description": "jkh talks to three agents across 5+ channels (omgjkh Slack, offtera Slack, Mattermost, Telegram incoming, and more). Each agent only knows what jkh told *it* on *its* channel \u2014 no shared view. Proposal: maintain a shared jkh-sessions.md / jkh-state.json on MinIO (agents/shared/jkh-state.json) that any agent updates after a significant conversation with jkh. Fields: last_seen_channel, last_seen_ts, recent_context (rolling summary), active_topics[], open_asks[], telegram_id. Other agents read it on each heartbeat cycle so they have situational awareness without jkh repeating himself. Conflict resolution: last-write-wins on ts, with each agent appending rather than overwriting context. jkh Telegram ID: 7601676269 (to be added to config when Telegram channel goes live).",
      "notes": "jkh requested this 2026-03-19T05:58 PDT. Already have jkh-sessions.md on Rocky (memory/jkh-sessions.md) but it is not shared cross-agent.",
      "channel": "mattermost",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "coordination",
        "jkh",
        "high-priority"
      ],
      "claimedBy": "natasha",
      "claimedAt": null,
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 3,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-19T19:37:00.000Z",
      "result": "jkh-state.json written to MinIO agents/shared/jkh-state.json \u2014 schema v1, per-agent last_seen + jkh context fields, last-write-wins."
    },
    {
