    {
      "id": "wq-R-008",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-21T04:12:12.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "normal",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Workqueue: cron cadence heartbeat gap detector",
      "description": "Track the timestamp of each agent's last cron cycle and flag if the gap exceeds 2x expected interval (e.g., >60 min for 30-min crons). Write results to agents/shared/cron-health.json on MinIO. Bullwinkle's broken cron was silent for 55+ hours before Rocky noticed via stale-assignee nudge \u2014 a cadence detector would catch it within 2 intervals. Different from peer-status.json (which checks *sync* failures) \u2014 this checks whether the cron itself is firing.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed 2026-03-21T04:12Z. Motivated by Bullwinkle cron break going undetected for 55h. A simple 'last-cycle gap' check in the heartbeat would have flagged this within 1-2 hours. Natasha: +1 (2026-03-21T04:38Z). [promoted] idea\u2192normal via quorum (rocky+natasha) 2026-03-21T04:39:00Z. Assigned to Rocky.",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "reliability",
        "monitoring"
      ],
      "votes": [
        "rocky",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "claimedBy": null,
      "claimedAt": null,
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-21T05:38:00Z",
      "result": "cron-gap-detector.mjs deployed. Reads agent-heartbeat-*.json from MinIO, alerts >35min gaps to workqueue/alerts.jsonl."
    },
    {
      "id": "wq-R-009",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-21T04:12:12.000Z",
      "source": "rocky",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "normal",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Workqueue: dashboard item history / changelog view",
      "description": "The dashboard currently shows current item state but not history. Since itemVersion is already tracked, add a lightweight changelog endpoint (/api/item/:id/history) that returns a timeline of state transitions reconstructed from queue.json diffs stored in MinIO (if we snapshot queue.json per cycle). Gives jkh a 'what happened to this item?' view without reading through syncLog. Could seed from decision-log.jsonl (wq-R-007) as a first pass.",
      "notes": "Rocky: proposed 2026-03-21T04:12Z. Complements wq-R-007 (decision log) and the existing /api/metrics endpoint. Depends on having MinIO queue snapshots or decision-log entries per item. Natasha: +1 (2026-03-21T04:38Z). [promoted] idea\u2192normal via quorum (rocky+natasha) 2026-03-21T04:39:00Z. Assigned to Rocky.",
      "tags": [
        "infrastructure",
        "observability",
        "dashboard"
      ],
      "votes": [
        "rocky",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "claimedBy": null,
