      "title": "[Aviation] Fix chronic Deploy CI failure \u2014 TypeScript compile errors in flight-planner",
      "description": "The 'Deploy Aviation Applications' workflow has been failing on every run since at least March 2 (30/30 runs failed). Root cause: TypeScript compile errors in apps/flight-planner/src/ \u2014 including type mismatches in FlightPlan interface (missing origin/destination/speed/altitude/id/name fields), undefined ProcedureSelection type, implicit any types in ProcedureSelection.tsx, and unused import warnings treated as errors. These are pre-existing and NOT from recent agent work. Need: Fix FlightPlan type definition to match usage, add proper types to ProcedureSelection.tsx, clean unused imports.",
      "notes": "Identified 2026-03-22T05:06Z by Rocky during CI audit. 30+ consecutive failures since 2026-03-02. Not caused by recent Boris/Rocky AI-explainer work \u2014 those TS errors predate it. Specific errors: FlightPlan missing properties (origin/dest/speed/alt/id/name), ProcedureSelection.tsx implicit any params, unused React import in G1000Controls.tsx.",
