      "title": "[jordanhubbard/webmux] Issue #9: feat: First-class Claude CLI session management + AI assistant panel",
      "description": "GitHub issue in jordanhubbard/webmux.\n\nIssue body:\n## Summary\n\nwebmux is the perfect platform for Claude CLI sessions \u2014 it already handles persistent terminal sessions in the browser. This issue tracks two related AI features:\n\n### 1. Claude CLI Session Template\n\nA new session type: **Claude Session**. When a user creates a Claude session:\n- Opens a tmux pane with Claude CLI pre-configured (`claude` or `claude-code`)\n- Guides the SSO auth flow in the UI (shows a panel: 'Click the link below, log in with your SSO, then paste the credential back')",
