    {
      "id": "wq-USER-1774228053758",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-23T01:07:33.758Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Scout dedup fix: suppress repeat-wave github items at source",
      "description": "The github scout is filing the same items every hour (loom CI, aviation todos, webmux features, rocky readme, etc). Bullwinkle is correctly killing duplicates but this wastes ~12 items/wave. Fix: before filing, scout should check if a scout_key already exists in the queue (completed OR pending) and skip re-filing. This would reduce noise significantly.",
      "notes": "",
      "tags": [
        "scout",
        "dedup",
        "infrastructure",
        "idea"
      ],
      "votes": [],
      "claimedBy": "rocky",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-24T01:04:03Z",
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 1,
      "lastAttempt": null,
      "completedAt": "2026-03-24T01:05:46Z",
      "result": "Investigation complete. Server-side scout_key dedup is already implemented in rcc/api/index.mjs (checks both items[] and completed[] on POST /api/queue). Client-side dedup also exists in pump.mjs via itemAlreadyExists(). Historical duplicates exist in completed[] from before the fix landed but no new dupes are being created. Current queue is clean \u2014 16 scout_keys have historical dupes (all in completed/closed status) but 0 active duplicates. No code change needed; fix was already applied.",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-23T22:04:50.270Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-23T22:03:00Z\""
