    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774440356488",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-25T12:05:56.488Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Slack App integration \u2014 inbound event handling (complete the loop)",
      "description": "Current state: CCC has outbound-only Slack integration (/api/slack/send, channel provisioning, context lookup). There is NO inbound path \u2014 no app_mention handling, no slash commands, no OAuth, no event subscriptions. This is worse than nothing: CCC can post to channels but cannot hear back, creating a one-way monologue with no feedback or control.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Do NOT expose or promote the current Slack integration to users until this is complete.\n\nWork required:\n1. Create Slack App manifest (scopes: chat:write, app_mentions:read, commands, channels:manage, channels:read, users:read)\n2. Add /api/slack/events endpoint to CCC API \u2014 verify Slack signing secret, handle url_verification challenge\n3. Handle app_mention events \u2014 route to agent brain, post reply in thread\n4. Handle slash commands (/rcc status, /rcc queue, /rcc ask <question>)\n5. Wire responses through agent capability routing (right agent replies in right channel)\n6. Install to omgjkh.slack.com first for testing \u2014 do NOT install to offtera until validated\n7. Add SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET to .env\n\nTest scenario: @Rocky what is in the queue? \u2192 CCC receives mention \u2192 brain processes \u2192 Rocky replies in thread.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-25T13:04:38.480Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-25T13:03:00Z\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-25T14:02:20.459Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"pending\"; claimedBy: \"rocky\" \u2192 null; claimedAt: \"2026-03-25T13:03:00Z\" \u2192 null"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-25T14:02:43.277Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-25T14:00:00Z\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-25T14:06:00.183Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Audit found inbound Slack event handling was ALREADY fully implemented in rcc/api/index.mjs: /api/slack/events (url_verification, app_mention with brain routing, DM handling, signature verification, dedup), /api/slack/commands (/rcc status|queue|ask|help). Added missing deployment artifacts: rcc/slack/manifest.json (Slack App manifest with scopes, event subs, slash commands) + SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET to deploy/.env.template. Commit 429fa4e pushed to jordanhubbard/rockyandfriends. Next step for jkh: create Slack App at api.slack.com using the manifest, then set SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET + SLACK_TOKEN in ~/.rcc/.env and reload rcc-api.service.\""
        }
      ],
