    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774539004802",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-26T15:30:04.802Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Agent migration system \u2014 Django-style schema migrations for agent config/state",
      "description": "Agents accumulate config debt over time (env vars rename, new services added, old ones removed). Need a migration system where:\n\n1. Migrations live in the repo (e.g. `migrations/0001_add_milvus.js`, `migrations/0002_rename_azure_sas.js`)\n2. Each agent tracks which migrations have been applied (in a local state file, e.g. `~/.openclaw/migrations-applied.json`)\n3. On startup or `agent-update` hook, agent checks for unapplied migrations and runs them in order\n4. Migrations can: rename/add/remove env vars, update config file schema, create directories, seed data, etc.\n5. Idempotent \u2014 safe to run twice\n6. `agent-rtx` incident (2026-03-26): had stale env vars (MINIO_ENDPOINT etc.), missing new ones (SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET, NVIDIA_API_KEY, MILVUS_ADDRESS). Had to manually fix. This would have been automatic.\n\nInspired by Django migrations. Could also draw from Flyway/Liquibase patterns.\n\nRelated: agent-update hook should trigger: (1) git pull, (2) run pending migrations, (3) restart services if needed.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-26T16:04:11.984Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
