    {
      "id": "wq-META-directives-001",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T03:53:11.696Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Create shared DIRECTIVES.md \u2014 meta-directives all agents must follow",
      "description": "jkh directive 2026-03-26: Accumulate meta-directives across all agents. All agents should follow these directives.\n\nThe problem: directives are currently scattered \u2014 some in HEARTBEAT.md (Rocky), some in agent-specific AGENTS.md, some only spoken in chat and never persisted.\n\n**What to build:**\n1. Create /home/jkh/.openclaw/workspace/DIRECTIVES.md \u2014 shared file, all agents read this\n2. Populate with all known meta-directives (from HEARTBEAT.md, AGENTS.md, chat history, memory files)\n3. Known directives to include:\n   - 24/7 mode \u2014 no quiet hours, no sleep mode (2026-03-21)\n   - Keep working on tasks across heartbeats \u2014 do NOT go passive (2026-03-26)\n   - Always create tasks for things found that require work (2026-03-26)\n   - Follow per-agent HEARTBEAT.md active task block \u2014 resume every heartbeat\n   - Boris routing rules (wq-B-009)\n   - Budget pause threshold (>8 active items)\n4. Add DIRECTIVES.md to deploy/agent-pull.sh so it syncs to all agents on pull\n5. Each agent adds a line to their HEARTBEAT.md: read DIRECTIVES.md every session\n6. Push to rockyandfriends so Bullwinkle/Natasha/Boris pull it on next sync",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T03:53:27.769Z",
