    {
      "id": "wq-CCC-bootstrap-001",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T04:25:03.709Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "CCC: agent bootstrap API + deploy key store + bootstrap.sh",
      "description": "jkh directive 2026-03-26: CCC should be the single source of admin state. Agents only need an admin token to bootstrap \u2014 CCC hands them everything else.\n\n## Design\n\n### CCC as key store\nRCC stores the GitHub deploy key and repo SSH URL. Agents never need GitHub credentials directly \u2014 they get them from CCC at bootstrap time.\n\n### New CCC endpoints\n\n**POST /api/keys/github**\n- Auth: admin token (RCC_ADMIN_TOKEN env var, separate from agent tokens)\n- Body: {repoUrl: \"git@github.com:jordanhubbard/rockyandfriends.git\", deployKey: \"<PEM string>\", label: \"optional\"}\n- Stores key in rcc/data/github-key.json (chmod 600)\n- Returns {ok, keyId}\n\n**GET /api/keys/github**\n- Auth: admin token\n- Returns {ok, repoUrl, deployKey, label, registeredAt}\n\n**POST /api/bootstrap/token**\n- Auth: admin token\n- Body: {agent: \"boris\", ttlSeconds: 3600}\n- Generates a single-use bootstrap token, stores in memory with TTL + agent name\n- Returns {ok, bootstrapToken, expiresAt}\n\n**GET /api/bootstrap?agent=boris**\n- Auth: bootstrap token (one-time use, expires after first successful call)\n- Returns: {ok, repoUrl, deployKey, agentToken, repoSshUrl}\n- agentToken = the static agent token for this agent name (from agents.json or newly generated)\n- Marks bootstrap token consumed after response\n\n### deploy/bootstrap.sh\nSingle-command agent bootstrap:\n```\ncurl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jordanhubbard/rockyandfriends/main/deploy/bootstrap.sh | \\\n  bash -s -- --rcc=http://146.190.134.110:8789 --token=<bootstrap-token> --agent=boris\n```\n\nScript steps:\n1. Clone repo via HTTPS (public, no auth): git clone https://github.com/jordanhubbard/rockyandfriends.git ~/.rcc/workspace\n2. Call GET /api/bootstrap?agent=$AGENT with bootstrap token\n3. Write deploy key to ~/.ssh/rcc-deploy-key (chmod 600)\n4. Write ~/.ssh/config entry for github.com with IdentityFile pointing to key\n5. Rewrite .git/config remote origin from HTTPS to SSH URL from CCC\n6. Verify: git fetch origin (should work with new key)\n7. Write agent token to ~/.rcc/.env as RCC_AGENT_TOKEN\n8. Write RCC_URL, AGENT_NAME, AGENT_HOST to ~/.rcc/.env\n9. Post first heartbeat to confirm bootstrap complete\n10. Print success summary\n\n### Fork support\nThe stored repoUrl in CCC can be any fork (git@github.com:someNCP/rockyandfriends.git). The bootstrap script does not hardcode the upstream repo URL \u2014 it always gets it from CCC. To support multiple forks, CCC can store multiple keys keyed by label.\n\n### Security notes\n- RCC_ADMIN_TOKEN is a separate env var, never shared with agents\n- Bootstrap tokens are single-use and short-lived (default 1h)\n- Deploy key never stored on agent disk unencrypted (or if it is, mode 600, in ~/.ssh/)\n- GET /api/bootstrap logs the agent name and IP for audit trail\n\n### Files to create/modify\n- rcc/api/index.mjs: add /api/keys/github + /api/bootstrap/token + /api/bootstrap endpoints\n- rcc/data/github-key.json: key store (gitignored)\n- deploy/bootstrap.sh: the one-command bootstrap script\n- .gitignore: add rcc/data/github-key.json\n- rcc/ONBOARDING.md: update with new bootstrap flow\n- DIRECTIVES.md: add note that bootstrap.sh is the canonical onboarding path",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T04:53:08.131Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\""
