    {
      "id": "wq-MIGRATE-agents-legacy-001",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T04:46:50.783Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Migrate legacy agents (Bullwinkle, Natasha, Boris, RTX) to current rockyandfriends baseline",
      "description": "Several agents were bootstrapped before the current rockyandfriends repo structure existed. They have divergent workspace layouts, missing files, old tooling, and no awareness of new infrastructure (DIRECTIVES.md, /api/scout, /api/vector/context, /api/ideation, etc.).\n\n## Problem inventory per agent\n\n**Bullwinkle (puck, macOS)**\n- Has rockyandfriends remote but may be behind main\n- Missing: DIRECTIVES.md, new CCC endpoints, Milvus ingest wiring\n- deploy/agent-pull.sh may be on old version (pre-scout, pre-ideation)\n- Static token: already has one (Mattermost-based auth), but needs CCC static token in .env\n\n**Natasha (sparky, Linux/Blackwell)**\n- natasha/local-work was merged to main tonight but she may not have pulled\n- Missing: DIRECTIVES.md awareness, new CCC endpoints\n- Has Milvus locally but may not have ingest wiring\n- Static token: was using dynamic registration \u2014 needs CCC static token\n\n**Boris (sweden-l40, Linux/x86)**\n- Has never successfully onboarded to CCC heartbeat (wq-BORIS-onboard-001 still open)\n- Missing: deploy/agent-pull.sh, DIRECTIVES.md, all new CCC tooling\n- Static token: NOW EXISTS \u2014 rcc-agent-boris-static-32dffce5703df1f00253f7f1 (in RCC_AUTH_TOKENS)\n- Needs: bootstrap.sh run (once wq-CCC-bootstrap-001 is built) OR manual sync\n\n**Agent RTX (jordanh-rtx, Linux/x86)**\n- Same situation as Boris \u2014 never successfully onboarded\n- Static token: rcc-agent-rtx-static-fba00269e0759e265696f5d5\n\n## Migration approach (before bootstrap.sh exists)\n\nFor each agent, the migration is:\n1. `git pull origin main` \u2014 get current rockyandfriends baseline\n2. Verify DIRECTIVES.md is present and readable\n3. Update .env: add RCC_AGENT_TOKEN (static token), RCC_URL=http://146.190.134.110:8789\n4. Update deploy/agent-pull.sh to current version from repo\n5. Post heartbeat to CCC to confirm online: POST /api/heartbeat/{agent}\n6. Verify /api/agents/status shows agent as online\n7. Run node rcc/scripts/ingest-memory.mjs to seed Milvus with local memory files\n8. Confirm /api/vector/context returns results\n\n## Migration approach (after bootstrap.sh exists)\n\nOnce wq-CCC-bootstrap-001 is done, the migration for Boris/RTX is just:\n```\ncurl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jordanhubbard/rockyandfriends/main/deploy/bootstrap.sh | \\\n  bash -s -- --rcc=http://146.190.134.110:8789 --token=<bootstrap-token> --agent=boris\n```\n\nFor Bullwinkle/Natasha (already have the repo): simpler migration script that just syncs and verifies.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. deploy/migrate.sh \u2014 migration script for agents that already have a workspace (git pull + .env update + heartbeat verify). Takes --agent and --rcc-token args.\n2. Mattermost/Slack message to each agent with their static token and migration instructions\n3. Verify all 4 agents appear in GET /api/agents/status after migration\n4. Update DIRECTIVES.md with note that migration is complete and bootstrap.sh is the canonical path going forward\n5. Close wq-BORIS-onboard-001 and related SYNC/MIGRATE/RUST tasks once Boris is actually online\n\n## Dependency\nwq-CCC-bootstrap-001 should land first for Boris/RTX. Bullwinkle and Natasha can migrate immediately via git pull + .env update.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T04:53:08.190Z",
          "author": "api",
