    {
      "id": "wq-FIX-migrate-macos-sed",
      "itemVersion": 2,
      "created": "2026-03-27T04:59:46.969Z",
      "source": "bullwinkle",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "fix: deploy/migrate.sh macOS sed -i compatibility",
      "description": "migrate.sh uses Linux sed -i syntax. On macOS (Darwin), sed -i requires an empty string argument: sed -i \"\" \"s|...|...|\" instead of sed -i \"s|...|...|\".\n\nFix: detect OS in migrate.sh and use the correct sed -i variant. Pattern:\n  if [[ \"$(uname)\" == \"Darwin\" ]]; then SED_INPLACE=\"sed -i \"; else SED_INPLACE=\"sed -i\"; fi\nThen use $SED_INPLACE throughout.\n\nReported by Bullwinkle after successful macOS migration with manual workaround.",
      "notes": "Fixed immediately \u2014 SED_I() wrapper detects Darwin vs Linux. Committed 82a4639.",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T05:00:15.119Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"completed\"; notes: \"\" \u2192 \"Fixed immediately \u2014 SED_I() wrapper detects Darwin vs Linux. Committed 82a4639.\""
        }
      ],
