    {
      "id": "wq-CCC-secrets-design-001",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-27T11:02:06.944Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "CCC as sole secrets store \u2014 harden the design so agent admin token is the ONLY shared secret",
      "description": "jkh directive 2026-03-27: The canonical design is:\n\n- CCC is the sole holder of all secrets: GitHub deploy key, Slack app token, Mattermost credentials, Milvus address, MinIO creds, etc.\n- The ONLY thing an agent and CCC need to share is the CCC admin token (or a short-lived bootstrap token derived from it).\n- Once an agent presents that token to CCC, CCC hands it everything else it needs to operate.\n- Agents do NOT store long-lived secrets locally (except the admin/bootstrap token itself).\n\n## Audit and enforce this design:\n\n1. **Audit current state** \u2014 scan .rcc/.env on do-host1 and rockyandfriends deploy/.env.template. Identify every secret currently stored on agents that should instead be fetched from CCC.\n\n2. **CCC secret registry** \u2014 ensure CCC has endpoints for all secrets agents currently need:\n   - GET /api/secrets/github (deploy key + repo URL) \u2713 (wq-CCC-bootstrap-001)\n   - GET /api/secrets/slack (bot token + signing secret)\n   - GET /api/secrets/mattermost (server URL + token per agent)\n   - GET /api/secrets/minio (endpoint + access key + secret key)\n   - GET /api/secrets/milvus (address)\n   - GET /api/secrets/nvidia (API key / inference gateway URL)\n   - Generic: GET /api/secrets/:key for arbitrary KV\n\n3. **Bootstrap flow audit** \u2014 verify deploy/bootstrap.sh + deploy/migrate.sh correctly:\n   - Accept only the admin token as input\n   - Fetch all other secrets from CCC after auth\n   - Write them to ~/.rcc/.env (not hardcoded in scripts)\n   - Never log or expose the admin token\n\n4. **Secret rotation** \u2014 when a secret is rotated in CCC, agents should be able to re-fetch on next heartbeat without re-bootstrapping. Add: POST /api/secrets/:key (admin-only write), and agent-pull.sh should call a secrets-sync step.\n\n5. **Token hierarchy clarification** \u2014 document the token model:\n   - RCC_ADMIN_TOKEN: jkh-only, stored in CCC .env, never distributed to agents\n   - RCC_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN: short-lived, single-use, generated by admin for new agent onboarding\n   - RCC_AGENT_TOKEN: long-lived per-agent token CCC returns at bootstrap, used for normal API calls\n   - All other secrets: fetched from CCC using agent token, never pre-distributed\n\n6. **DIRECTIVES.md update** \u2014 add: agents must not store secrets outside of what CCC provides. If a secret is needed and not in ~/.rcc/.env, fetch it from CCC.\n\n7. **Security model doc** \u2014 write rcc/docs/security-model.md capturing this hierarchy clearly for future agent onboarding.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T11:04:02.962Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-27T11:02:00Z\""
