    {
      "id": "wq-SQUIRRELBUS-exec-001",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T16:58:19.605Z",
      "source": "jkh",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "ClawBus: CCC-signed remote code execution across all agents",
      "description": "## Goal\n\nAllow CCC to broadcast Node.js code to all connected agents via ClawBus, have each agent execute it in a sandboxed context, and return results. This enables Rocky (or jkh) to patch all running instances \u2014 Rocky, Bullwinkle, Natasha, Boris \u2014 without SSH or manual intervention.\n\n## Security model (CRITICAL \u2014 get this right)\n\nOnly code originating from CCC and bearing a valid HMAC signature may be executed. Agents must verify the signature before running anything. Unsigned or tampered payloads are silently dropped and logged.\n\n- **Signing key:** Shared secret stored in CCC secrets store as `SQUIRRELBUS_TOKEN` (already exists). Each agent has it in `~/.rcc/.env`.\n- **Signature:** HMAC-SHA256 over the canonical JSON payload (deterministic key sort, no whitespace). Included as `sig` field in the message envelope.\n- **Verification:** Each agent recomputes HMAC and compares. Reject on mismatch.\n- **No eval of arbitrary strings:** Use `vm.runInNewContext()` with a restricted context \u2014 no `require` by default, explicit allowlist of safe modules (`fs` read-only subset, `fetch`, `path`).\n- **Timeout:** Hard 10s execution limit per payload.\n- **Audit log:** Every execution attempt (pass or fail) logged to `~/.rcc/logs/remote-exec.jsonl` with timestamp, payload hash, result, and agent name.\n\n## Message envelope (ClawBus message type: `rcc.exec`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"rcc.exec\",\n  \"id\": \"exec-<uuid>\",\n  \"ts\": \"<ISO-8601>\",\n  \"target\": \"all | rocky | boris | ...\",\n  \"code\": \"<Node.js source \u2014 single expression or IIFE>\",\n  \"sig\": \"<HMAC-SHA256 hex of canonical JSON minus sig field>\",\n  \"replyTo\": \"<optional: mattermost channel or agent DM to post result>\"\n}\n```\n\n## CCC API additions\n\n- `POST /api/exec` \u2014 admin-only. Accepts `{ target, code, replyTo }`. Signs payload with SQUIRRELBUS_TOKEN, broadcasts via ClawBus. Returns `{ ok: true, execId }`.\n- `GET /api/exec/:id` \u2014 fetch result of a past exec by ID (stored in `data/exec-log.jsonl`).\n- `POST /api/exec/:id/result` \u2014 agents post their execution results here (auth: agent token).\n\n## Agent-side additions\n\nEach agent subscribes to ClawBus `rcc.exec` messages. On receipt:\n1. Verify `target` matches agent name or is `\"all\"`\n2. Verify HMAC signature \u2014 drop and log on mismatch\n3. Execute in sandboxed `vm.runInNewContext` with 10s timeout\n4. Capture stdout, return value, or error\n5. POST result to `RCC_URL/api/exec/:id/result` with agent token auth\n6. If `replyTo` is set, post result summary to that channel\n\nImplementation: `rcc/exec/index.mjs` (shared library), `rcc/exec/agent-listener.mjs` (agent-side).\n\n## Example use cases\n\n```js\n// Patch model config across all agents\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst p = process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/openclaw.json';\nconst c = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, 'utf8'));\nc.agents.defaults.model = 'nvidia/azure/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6';\nfs.writeFileSync(p, JSON.stringify(c, null, 2));\nreturn 'patched';\n\n// Check disk space on all agents\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\nreturn execSync('df -h /').toString().trim();\n```\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. `rcc/exec/index.mjs` \u2014 signing/verification library\n2. `rcc/exec/agent-listener.mjs` \u2014 agent-side ClawBus subscriber + executor\n3. `POST /api/exec`, `GET /api/exec/:id`, `POST /api/exec/:id/result` in `rcc/api/index.mjs`\n4. `data/exec-log.jsonl` \u2014 append-only exec result log on CCC\n5. Wire `agent-listener.mjs` into each agent's pull loop or as standalone persistent process\n6. `rcc/docs/remote-exec.md` \u2014 feature doc, security model, example payloads\n7. `tests/api/exec.test.mjs` \u2014 signing, verification, execution, timeout, bad-sig rejection\n\n## Commit\n```bash\ngit add rcc/exec/ rcc/api/index.mjs rcc/docs/remote-exec.md tests/\ngit commit -m \"feat(rcc): ClawBus remote code execution with HMAC signing\"\ngit push origin main\n```",
      "notes": "jkh directive 2026-03-27. Security model is non-negotiable \u2014 no unsigned code execution ever. Rocky owns CCC so implements the server side; all agents need the listener wired in. SQUIRRELBUS_TOKEN already exists in the secrets store.",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T17:04:06.516Z",
