      "description": "instar/src/templates/scripts/serendipity-capture.sh: sub-agents doing focused tasks discover adjacent things worth capturing, but pursuing them breaks focus. If uncaptured, insight is lost.\n\nProtocol: serendipity-capture.sh --title ... --description ... --category (bug/improvement/feature/pattern/refactor/security) --rationale ... --readiness (idea-only/partially-implemented/implementation-complete/tested)\n\nSafety baked in: rate limit (max 5/session), secret scanning (14 patterns), HMAC signing per finding, patch size limit 10KB, path traversal check, atomic writes (tmp + fsync + rename).\n\nRCC relevance: When Boris or Natasha are doing deep GPU work and notice something adjacent to CCC architecture, no clean way to capture it without breaking focus. This feeds directly into our workqueue as idea items.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/templates/scripts/serendipity-capture.sh",
