      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-09",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:12.877Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "low",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "STEAL THIS: free-text-guard.sh \u2014 PreToolUse hook for AskUserQuestion misuse",
      "description": "instar/.claude/hooks/free-text-guard.sh: blocks AskUserQuestion when the question expects free-text input (passwords, emails, tokens).\n\nProblem: Claude training pressure makes it prefer AskUserQuestion for collecting input, but that tool adds multi-choice escape hatches beneath the input field \u2014 confusing UX for credentials.\n\nFix: BLOCK for free-text questions. Correct approach: output question as plain text, STOP, wait for user's next message.\n\nDistinguishes: free-text patterns (password, api key, token, enter your X) vs decision patterns (which, prefer, choose, would you) \u2014 allows decisions, blocks free-text collection.\n\nKey quote: Structure > Willpower: training pressure makes Claude prefer structured tools. Prompt instructions alone cannot reliably prevent this.\n\nRCC relevance: Direct steal. Prevents awkward UX in agent-human Slack/Telegram interactions.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/templates/hooks/free-text-guard.sh",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
