    {
      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-01",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:11.403Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Adopt: CoherenceGate \u2014 LLM-supervised response review pipeline",
      "description": "instar/src/core/CoherenceGate.ts implements a multi-layer response review pipeline that runs BEFORE a response reaches the user:\n  1. Policy Enforcement Layer (PEL) \u2014 deterministic hard blocks (no LLM cost)\n  2. Gate Reviewer \u2014 fast Haiku-tier triage: does this need full review?\n  3. 9 specialist parallel reviewers: conversational-tone, claim-provenance, settling-detection, context-completeness, capability-accuracy, url-validity, value-alignment, information-leakage, escalation-resolution\n  4. Normative 15-row decision matrix: PASS / WARN / BLOCK / retry / hold / fail-open\n  5. Canary corpus of known-bad messages for periodic reviewer health checks\n  6. Audit log with DSAR-compliant deletion\n\nKey insight: settling-detection catches agent giving up without trying alternatives. capability-accuracy catches false inability claims.\n\nRCC relevance: We have no response review layer. This could be a PostToolUse hook or openclaw hook wrapping outbound message sends.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/core/CoherenceGate.ts\nAlso: src/core/PolicyEnforcementLayer.ts, src/core/reviewers/*.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T20:04:20.167Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-27T20:03:00Z\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:04:48.331Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: claimedAt: \"2026-03-27T20:03:00Z\" \u2192 \"2026-03-27T21:03:00Z\""
