      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-02",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:11.590Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Adopt: ExternalOperationGate \u2014 LLM-supervised safety for destructive ops",
      "description": "instar/src/core/ExternalOperationGate.ts was born from a real incident: an agent deleted 200+ emails autonomously because nothing structurally distinguished reads from bulk deletes.\n\nArchitecture:\n  1. Static risk matrix: mutability x reversibility x scope -> risk level (low/medium/high/critical)\n  2. Config floor: per-service allow/block/read-only lists (structural, no LLM override)\n  3. LLM proportionality check (Haiku): Does this match user intent? NOTE: LLM never sees content being operated on \u2014 only metadata. Prevents prompt injection via email body.\n  4. Batch/bulk checkpoint system: pause after N items, report progress\n  5. AUTONOMY_PROFILES: supervised/collaborative/autonomous\n\nKey rules: bulk (>20 items) irreversible ops always require plan. Trust can never auto-escalate to autonomous.\n\nRCC relevance: We do zero risk classification on external ops. Same gap as the email incident.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/core/ExternalOperationGate.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T20:04:20.331Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-27T20:03:00Z\""
