      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-06",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:12.320Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "STEAL THIS: dangerous-command-guard.sh \u2014 Level 1/2 hook with self-verification",
      "description": "instar/src/templates/hooks/dangerous-command-guard.sh is a PreToolUse bash hook with two levels:\n\nLevel 1 (default): block + require user authorization before proceeding\nLevel 2 (autonomous): inject SELF-VERIFICATION prompt instead of blocking. Agent must reason: (1) Is this necessary? (2) Consequences if wrong? (3) Safer alternative? (4) Aligned with principles and intent?\n\nAlways-block (regardless of level): rm -rf /, mkfs, dd if=, fork bombs, --accept-data-loss, prisma migrate reset. Note: prisma migrate reset was added after a real production data loss incident (Portal 2026-02-22). Lessons baked in.\n\nThe Level 1->Level 2 progression is the path to autonomy. Structure > willpower.\n\nRCC relevance: Agents have sudo and full filesystem access on do-host1. Direct steal \u2014 copy, adapt patterns, install as hook.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/templates/hooks/dangerous-command-guard.sh",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
