      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-08",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:12.692Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "low",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Study: IntentDriftDetector \u2014 alignment drift detection from decision journals",
      "description": "instar/src/core/IntentDriftDetector.ts: fully deterministic (no LLM) drift detection comparing two time windows of decision journal data.\n\nDrift signals: conflict_spike (agent fighting with itself more), confidence_drop (decisions less certain), principle_shift (agent using different values), volume_change.\n\nAlso computes AlignmentScore (0-100) from journal health metrics.\n\nRequires: DecisionJournal \u2014 logs every significant decision with: principle_used, confidence, was_conflict, outcome.\n\nRCC relevance: As jkh travels and we operate autonomously for extended periods, drift detection is a valuable safety signal. Requires instrumenting agents to log decisions. Non-trivial but high value for autonomous multi-agent systems.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/core/IntentDriftDetector.ts\nAlso: src/core/DecisionJournal.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:53:50.501Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"natasha\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:55:31.382Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Study complete. Findings documented in docs/instar-studies/ (commit 9e53319). Both items: study-only, not immediately adoptable. IntentDriftDetector needs DecisionJournal prereq. Threadline superseded by ClawBus for our fleet; specific patterns (trust tiers, compute metering, delivery ACK) flagged for future ClawBus improvements.\""
        }
      ],
