      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-10",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:13.069Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "low",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Study: Threadline Protocol + OpenClawBridge \u2014 A2A messaging with crypto identity",
      "description": "instar/src/threadline/ is a full A2A communication protocol:\n  - Ed25519 cryptographic agent identity\n  - DNS-based agent discovery\n  - Trust bootstrap: word-based pairing codes, handshake protocol\n  - Circuit breaker for unhealthy agents\n  - Rate limiting per agent pair\n  - Compute metering per agent\n  - MCP server integration \u2014 agents expose tools to each other via MCP\n  - OpenClawBridge.ts \u2014 explicitly built to interop with OpenClaw (this is us!)\n  - Framework adapters: AutoGen, CrewAI, LangGraph, REST\n  - 1,817 tests across 52 test files\n\nThe OpenClawBridge is particularly interesting. instar already designed OpenClaw interop. Could inform Rocky/Bullwinkle/Natasha/Boris communication architecture.\n\nRCC relevance: Current agent comm = Mattermost DMs + Slack + workqueue polling. Threadline represents a more principled A2A layer. The crypto identity + circuit breaker patterns worth studying even if not adopting wholesale.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/tree/main/src/threadline\nKey: ThreadlineClient.ts, OpenClawBridge.ts, CircuitBreaker.ts, AgentTrustManager.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:53:50.648Z",
