      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-03",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:11.771Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Adopt: AdaptiveTrust \u2014 organic trust evolution per service/operation type",
      "description": "instar/src/core/AdaptiveTrust.ts implements trust as a living dimension tracked per-service x per-operation-type.\n\nExamples: 'I trust you with reading email but not deleting it'. '20 calendar ops without incident, stop asking'. 'After that incident, always ask before modifying emails'.\n\nThree change paths:\n  1. Earned: consistent successful ops auto-build trust (streak counter)\n  2. Granted: user explicitly says you don't need to ask me about X\n  3. Revoked: incident or explicit revocation\n\nSafety floor: trust can never auto-escalate to autonomous \u2014 only explicit user grant.\n\nIntegrates with ExternalOperationGate to dynamically update autonomy defaults.\n\nRCC relevance: Our workqueue has static priority/assignment but no trust model. An agent with 50 successful Slack tasks should be trusted differently than a new one. Could inform task assignment and autonomy levels.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/core/AdaptiveTrust.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:07:01.016Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-27T21:06:00Z\""
