      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636271360-04",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:31:11.959Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Adopt: WorkingMemoryAssembler \u2014 token-budgeted context assembly from memory layers",
      "description": "instar/src/memory/WorkingMemoryAssembler.ts solves: how do you inject the RIGHT context into a session without blowing the context window?\n\nAlgorithm: extract query terms from session trigger -> search semantic memory -> search episodic memory -> search person entities -> budget tokens across sources (knowledge=800, episodes=400, relationships=300, total=2000)\n\nTiered render strategy (key insight):\n  - Top 3: full content\n  - Next 7: compact (first sentence + confidence)\n  - Remainder: name-only list (Also related: X, Y, Z)\n\nSearch strategy: per-term OR-like search + full-query AND search, merged with score boosting for multi-term matches. Avoids FTS5 implicit-AND which is too restrictive.\n\nRCC relevance: Our memory_search returns raw results with no budget management. Sessions get flooded with context. This assembler pattern could wrap our Milvus queries to produce structured, token-budgeted context injections.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/memory/WorkingMemoryAssembler.ts",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T21:07:01.091Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-27T21:06:00Z\""
