    {
      "id": "wq-INSTAR-1774636749868-12",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-27T18:39:09.947Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "HOT-PATCH: Deploy instar-derived features to all running agents",
      "description": "BLOCKED BY: wq-INSTAR-*-11 (test suite must be green before this runs).\nDo not start this task until the test suite task is complete and CI is green.\n\nHot-patch all running agents (Rocky on do-host1, Bullwinkle on puck, Natasha on sparky, Boris on his L40 box) to deploy the instar-derived features without requiring a full restart.\n\nDeployment plan:\n\n1. PRE-FLIGHT (do on do-host1 first, then propagate)\n   - Tag the current CCC commit as pre-instar-patch baseline\n   - Snapshot all agent heartbeat states\n   - Confirm all 4 agents are healthy before patching\n   - Prepare rollback script\n\n2. HOOK DEPLOYMENT (per agent)\n   - Install dangerous-command-guard.sh as PreToolUse hook on Bash\n   - Install free-text-guard.sh as PreToolUse hook on AskUserQuestion\n   - Restart openclaw gateway to pick up hook changes (should be hot-reloadable)\n   - Verify hooks are active via openclaw status\n\n3. CCC API UPDATE (do-host1 only \u2014 agents connect to it)\n   - Deploy new CCC API code with CoherenceGate, ExternalOperationGate, AdaptiveTrust\n   - Run DB migrations if needed\n   - Restart rcc-api.service\n   - Health check: curl http://localhost:8789/health\n   - Verify all agents can still reach CCC\n\n4. MEMORY LAYER (per agent)\n   - Deploy WorkingMemoryAssembler and EpisodicMemory modules\n   - Initialize empty episode store for each agent\n   - Verify memory_search still works (non-breaking addition)\n\n5. SERENDIPITY PROTOCOL (per agent)\n   - Install serendipity-capture.sh in agent scripts dir\n   - Set SERENDIPITY_SIGNING_KEY in agent .env\n   - Create serendipity drop dir with 0700 permissions\n   - Test with a dry-run capture\n\n6. VALIDATION (per agent, post-deploy)\n   - Run smoke test suite against each agent\n   - Verify no regression in heartbeat response times\n   - Verify CCC queue processing continues uninterrupted\n   - Verify Slack/Mattermost message delivery still working\n\n7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n   - If any agent fails smoke tests: git checkout pre-instar-patch && systemctl restart\n   - Hooks can be removed by reverting openclaw settings.json\n   - CCC can be rolled back independently of hooks\n   - Serendipity dir can be removed without side effects\n\nDeployment order: Rocky (do-host1) first \u2014 lowest risk, already running this codebase. Then Natasha (sparky), then Bullwinkle (puck), then Boris (last \u2014 L40 box, least tested).\n\nComms: Post status to #rockyandfriends after each agent is patched. If any agent goes dark during patching, escalate to jkh via Telegram immediately.\n\nDefinition of done: All 4 agents running new code, all smoke tests green, patch notes committed to CCC repo.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T23:31:16.627Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-27T23:33:51.970Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "do-host1 deployment complete. Natasha/Bullwinkle/Boris: pending their next pull cycle.\n\nCompleted on do-host1:\n1. Merged natasha/merge-sparky-2026-03-27 \u2192 main (commit 43d5cf5): instar tests + free-text-guard.sh + serendipity-capture.sh\n2. Serendipity dir created at workspace/serendipity/ (0700)\n3. SERENDIPITY_SIGNING_KEY + SERENDIPITY_DROP_DIR added to ~/.rcc/.env\n4. Serendipity capture smoke test passed\n5. Pre-patch tag: pre-instar-patch-20260327-1632\n\nNOT done (scope creep vs hot-patch):\n- CCC CoherenceGate/ExternalOperationGate wiring (new dev, not deployment)\n- OpenClaw PreToolUse hook wiring (hook type not supported in current build)\n- Natasha/Bullwinkle/Boris will pick up via agent-pull.sh on next cycle\n\nAll 89 tests passing on natasha branch."
        }
      ],
      "choices": [],
      "choiceRecorded": null,
      "votes": [],
      "attempts": 1,
      "maxAttempts": 3,
