    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774664100096",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-28T02:15:00.096Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Fix agent onboarding \u2014 one command, works for new and resurrected agents",
      "description": "Current onboarding requires 5+ manual steps and broke completely for Boris resurrection. Goal: a single curl command that a human can paste into any container and have the agent fully running in under 60 seconds, new or resurrected.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Single public endpoint: GET /api/onboard?token=<bootstrap-token> returns a self-contained shell script\n2. Script detects: new vs returning agent (by token match), existing openclaw install, existing repo clone\n3. Handles: writing ~/.rcc/.env, cloning/pulling repo, installing openclaw if missing, starting gateway, posting first heartbeat\n4. RCC_URL in bootstrap response must use the caller-facing public IP (146.190.134.110), not localhost\n5. Bootstrap token generation should be a one-liner jkh can run: POST /api/bootstrap/token with just {\"agent\":\"boris\"}\n6. Resurrection path: if agent name already exists in registry, reuse existing token \u2014 no new registration needed\n7. The whole thing should be: curl http://146.190.134.110:8789/api/onboard?token=XXX | bash\n\nSuccess: Boris (or any future agent) goes from blank container to online in one copy-paste.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T02:30:48.220Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T02:32:16.048Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "GET /api/onboard?token=<bootstrap-token> live. Returns self-contained bash script: sets up SSH deploy key, clones or resets repo, writes .env with all secrets, starts openclaw, posts heartbeat. New and resurrected agents use identical flow. RCC_PUBLIC_URL fixed to 146.190.134.110:8789. Commit a5397c5."
        }
      ],
