    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774666149846",
      "itemVersion": 2,
      "created": "2026-03-28T02:49:09.846Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Dashboard v2: Geek View \u2014 distributed brain topology visualization",
      "description": "Full design spec already exists in branch feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view (rcc/docs/dashboard-v2-design.md, section 7). Implement as part of the Rust/WASM dashboard.\n\nGeek View = SVG topology map of the entire system with live traffic animation.\n\n## What It Shows\n- **Nodes (machines primary):** Rocky (do-host1), Bullwinkle (puck), Natasha (sparky), Boris (l40-sweden), plus shared services (Milvus, MinIO, SearXNG) as standalone nodes. External services (NVIDIA Gateway, GitHub, Mattermost, Slack x2, Telegram) on the periphery.\n- **Service chips per machine:** Each agent node shows inline chips for services running on it (e.g. Rocky shows: CCC API :8789, Dashboard :8788, Brain, ClawBus hub, Tailscale proxy).\n- **Edges:** solid = persistent connection, dashed = on-demand call. Labels show protocol.\n- **Live traffic particles:** animated dots flow along edges on ClawBus events, heartbeats, brain requests.\n- **Node pulse:** pulse animation if active in last 5min. Color: \ud83d\udfe2 <5min, \ud83d\udfe1 5-30min, \ud83d\udd34 >30min.\n\n## Data Sources\n- GET /api/geek/topology \u2014 node/edge map + live status (heartbeats, uptime, queue depth)\n- GET /api/geek/stream \u2014 SSE for live traffic events (already partially implemented in the branch)\n- GET /api/heartbeats \u2014 for agent status\n\n## Traffic Log Panel\nBottom panel: last 20 events with timestamp, from\u2192to, type (heartbeat/bus_msg/brain_req).\n\n## Unanswered Message Queue\nFiltered ClawBus view: messages sent without response. 'Rocky \u2192 Bullwinkle: 12 unanswered' is a health signal.\n\n## Soul Commit Timeline\nPer-agent: last commit to souls/ repo dir. Show as a strip below each agent node.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- SVG preferred over Canvas (accessibility + CSS animations)\n- Static layout (hand-tuned, not force-directed) \u2014 see rough sketch in design spec\n- SSE reconnects automatically; falls back to 5s poll if SSE fails\n- Dark theme matching rest of dashboard\n- Branch feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view has partial implementation \u2014 review and port to Rust/WASM",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T02:50:06.960Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "Duplicate \u2014 closed"
        }
      ],
