    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774666930537",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-28T03:02:10.537Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Task completion callbacks \u2014 notify jkh on Slack when any agent completes a task",
      "description": "When any agent calls POST /api/item/:id/complete, CCC should automatically notify jkh on Slack. Currently completions are silent \u2014 jkh only finds out by checking the dashboard.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### CCC API side (post-completion hook)\nIn the /complete handler, after writing the queue, fire a non-blocking Slack notification:\n- Channel: DM to jkh (UDYR7H4SC on omgjkh.slack.com)\n- Format: '\u2705 *<title>* \u2014 completed by <agent>\\n<resolution or result, truncated to 200 chars>\\n_<id>_'\n- Only for items with priority != 'idea' (skip idea promotions/closures \u2014 too noisy)\n- Only for items where assignee != 'jkh' (jkh completing his own items is obvious)\n- Fire-and-forget: completion succeeds even if Slack call fails\n\n### Config\n- SLACK_NOTIFY_TOKEN \u2014 which bot token to use (default: OMGJKH_BOT)\n- SLACK_NOTIFY_USER \u2014 jkh's user ID (UDYR7H4SC)\n- CCC reads these from secrets/env; no hardcoding\n- Opt-out: if item has tag 'silent' or 'no-notify', skip\n\n### Scope\n- POST /api/item/:id/complete (new callback endpoints) \u2014 yes\n- POST /api/complete/:id (legacy dashboard endpoint) \u2014 yes, same hook\n- PATCH /api/item/:id with status=completed \u2014 yes\n- Auto-archive of stale items (expire-stale) \u2014 no (system action, not agent completion)\n\n### Deduplication\n- Track notified item IDs in memory (Map, cleared on restart) \u2014 don't double-notify if somehow called twice\n\n## Definition of Done\n- Rocky completes a test item, jkh receives a Slack DM within 5 seconds\n- Natasha completes a GPU task, jkh receives notification\n- Idea items and jkh-assigned items do NOT generate notifications\n- CCC API restart does not cause duplicate notifications for already-completed items",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T03:03:59.753Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"in-progress\"; claimedBy: null \u2192 \"rocky\"; claimedAt: null \u2192 \"2026-03-28T03:03:59Z\""
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T03:06:04.884Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "Already implemented in rcc/api/index.mjs (commit d96de2c). notifyJkhCompletion() fires on /complete, /api/item/:id with status=completed, and legacy /api/complete/:id. Sends Slack DM to UDYR7H4SC (omgjkh). Skips idea priority and jkh-assigned items. No-op if SLACK_BOT_TOKEN unset."
        }
      ],
      "choices": [],
      "choiceRecorded": null,
      "votes": [],
      "attempts": 0,
      "maxAttempts": 3,
      "claimedBy": "rocky",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-28T03:03:59Z",
