      "title": "Dashboard UI smoke tests \u2014 catch process.env and client-side regressions",
      "description": "The dashboard served process.env.OPERATOR_HANDLE directly in browser JS, causing a ReferenceError. We caught it manually. Need automated tests to catch this class of bug before it reaches jkh.\n\nRequired tests:\n1. Serve the dashboard HTML and assert zero occurrences of `process.env` in the response body\n2. Assert zero occurrences of `require(` or other Node-only globals in served HTML/JS\n3. Load the page in a headless browser (playwright or puppeteer) and assert no console errors on load\n4. Assert key UI sections render: agent cards, queue table, heartbeat status\n5. Run as part of CI (add to rcc/tests/run-tests.sh)\n\nBonus: add a pre-commit hook that greps for process.env inside template literals in server.mjs and fails if found.",
