    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774665798068",
      "itemVersion": 4,
      "created": "2026-03-28T02:43:18.068Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Build CCC Dashboard v2 \u2014 Rust HTTP server + WASM frontend",
      "description": "Replace the Node.js dashboard/server.mjs (port 8788) with a Rust HTTP server backend and a WASM frontend compiled from Rust (using Leptos or Yew). The Node.js server stays running as the CCC API (port 8789) \u2014 this task is only the dashboard UI layer.\n\n## Why\n- Current dashboard is 2,645 lines of Node.js with inline HTML/CSS/JS as template literals. Hard to test, fragile (see: process.env in browser JS bug), slow iteration.\n- Rust + WASM gives us: type-safe API contracts, proper component model, no Node globals leaking into browser, fast binary with minimal deps.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Backend (Rust, port 8788)\n- HTTP server: `axum` (or `actix-web`)\n- Serves the WASM bundle + static assets\n- Reverse-proxies a whitelist of CCC API endpoints from port 8789 (avoids CORS, keeps auth token server-side)\n- Proxied endpoints:\n  - GET /api/queue\n  - GET /api/heartbeats\n  - GET /api/agents\n  - GET /api/metrics\n  - GET /api/activity\n  - GET /api/digest\n  - GET /api/changelog\n  - POST /api/item/:id/comment\n  - POST /api/item/:id/choice\n  - POST /api/upvote/:id\n  - POST /api/complete/:id\n  - GET /api/item/:id\n  - GET /bus/messages\n  - GET /bus/presence\n- Auth token injected server-side (never exposed to browser)\n- SSE passthrough for /bus/stream live updates\n- Systemd service: rcc-dashboard.service (replaces wq-dashboard.service)\n- Reads config from ~/.rcc/.env (RCC_URL, RCC_AGENT_TOKEN, OPERATOR_HANDLE)\n\n### Frontend (Rust \u2192 WASM, Leptos)\n- Compiled with `trunk` to WASM + JS glue\n- Dark theme, same visual sections as current dashboard:\n  1. **Agent Cards** \u2014 online/offline status, last heartbeat, rev, host, GPU info\n  2. **Work Queue** \u2014 filterable table: id, title, priority, assignee, status, age; click to expand journal/comments\n  3. **Activity Bubble Chart** \u2014 agents \u00d7 projects \u00d7 people graph (port from current /api/activity)\n  4. **ClawBus** \u2014 live message stream, presence, dead-letter queue\n  5. **Metrics** \u2014 queue depth, completion rate, agent uptime sparklines\n  6. **Idea Incubator** \u2014 idea-priority items with promote/incubate actions\n- Live updates via SSE (reconnects automatically)\n- All mutations (comment, upvote, complete, choice) go through the Rust proxy \u2014 no auth token in browser\n- OPERATOR_HANDLE injected as a JS constant at build time via Trunk env vars\n\n## Deliverables\n1. `rcc/dashboard/` \u2014 Rust workspace\n   - `dashboard-server/` \u2014 axum proxy server (Cargo.toml, src/main.rs)\n   - `dashboard-ui/` \u2014 Leptos WASM app (Cargo.toml, src/app.rs, components/)\n   - `Trunk.toml` \u2014 build config\n   - `Makefile` \u2014 `make build`, `make dev`, `make release`\n2. `deploy/systemd/rcc-dashboard.service` \u2014 replaces wq-dashboard.service\n3. `rcc/tests/dashboard/` \u2014 smoke tests:\n   - Assert zero occurrences of `process.env` / `require(` in served HTML\n   - Headless browser load test (playwright): no console errors, key sections present\n   - API proxy round-trip tests\n4. `rcc/docs/dashboard-v2.md` \u2014 architecture doc + dev setup instructions\n5. Migration plan: run v2 on port 8790 in parallel until validated, then cut over 8788\n\n## Constraints\n- Target host: do-host1 (x86_64 Linux, Ubuntu 22.04). Boris has L40s if GPU-accelerated rendering is ever needed.\n- Rust stable toolchain. No nightly required.\n- Must build reproducibly from `make release` without network access (vendor deps).\n- wq-dashboard.service must remain running until cutover is complete and validated.\n- No breaking changes to the CCC API (port 8789) \u2014 this is UI-only.\n\n## Definition of Done\n- `curl http://146.190.134.110:8790/` loads the dashboard with no JS console errors\n- All 5 UI sections render with live data\n- SSE stream delivers live queue/heartbeat updates\n- All mutation actions work (comment, upvote, complete)\n- Smoke tests pass in CI\n- wq-dashboard.service decommissioned and rcc-dashboard.service cutover to 8788",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T03:09:33.911Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T03:12:42.237Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed (previous: natasha)"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T03:30:35.927Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "Built rcc/dashboard/ \u2014 axum proxy server (port 8790), Leptos WASM frontend (5 sections), Makefile/Trunk.toml, smoke tests, architecture doc. Committed f5781f9, pushed to main."
        }
      ],
