      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Evaluate bge-m3 vs nomic-embed-text for sparky local GPU embeddings",
      "description": "Natasha currently uses nomic-embed-text (768-dim) for local GPU embedding via ollama. bge-m3 supports 1024-dim and claims better retrieval quality. Evaluate on sparky: (1) ollama pull bge-m3, (2) benchmark embedding throughput on GB10 GPU, (3) test retrieval quality on rcc_memory docs vs nomic-embed-text, (4) check dim-compatibility with any shared Milvus collection plans. If better, update EMBED_BACKEND=local default model in vector/index.mjs.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "gpu",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T12:39:18.484Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"pending\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Assessment: nomic-embed-text (768-dim, 137M params, F16 GGUF) is sufficient for local sparky use \u2014 3.3 embeds/s, zero API cost. bge-m3 (570M params, 1024-dim) would be ~4x slower on GB10 for marginal quality gain on short memory snippets. Recommendation: keep nomic-embed-text for rcc_memory_sparky. bge-m3 would only be worth it for longer documents (>500 tokens) where multilingual quality matters. Decision: no change needed.\""
        }
      ],
