      "id": "wq-NAT-1774706923339",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-28T14:08:43.443Z",
      "source": "natasha",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "medium",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Fix ClawBus /bus/send auth \u2014 agent tokens rejected with 401",
      "description": "Natasha's RCC_AGENT_TOKEN (rcc-agent-natasha-*) is rejected with 401 when POSTing to both http://100.89.199.14:8788/bus/send and http://100.89.199.14:8789/bus/send. The /bus/* routes on port 8788 (dashboard) appear to require a different auth token than the agent token. Rocky fixed the endpoint (committed 582210e) but auth still fails from sparky. Investigate: (1) does /bus/send require dashboard token vs agent token? (2) is SQUIRRELBUS_TOKEN the correct auth header? (3) update WORKQUEUE_AGENT_NATASHA.md with the correct auth approach. This is blocking peer sync via ClawBus from sparky.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T14:31:08.007Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T14:32:32.986Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "Root cause: RCC_AUTH_TOKENS in dashboard .env did not include Natasha agent token. Fixed: added all registered agent tokens to RCC_AUTH_TOKENS, restarted dashboard. Tested: Natasha token now accepted on /bus/send. Auth header: Bearer $RCC_AGENT_TOKEN (same token used for CCC API at :8789)."
        }
      ],
