      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Natasha: GPU-accelerated trunk build for rcc/dashboard Rust/WASM on sparky",
      "description": "The rcc/dashboard Rust/WASM frontend (committed f5781f9) requires `trunk build` which is CPU-bound. Sparky has CUDA available but the bottleneck is actually the Rust compiler, not rendering. Proposal: set up a build cache (sccache) on sparky so repeated trunk builds reuse artifacts, cutting compile time from ~5min to <30s. Secondary: explore wasm-pack on sparky as alternative to trunk for lighter output. Both optimizations benefit the development loop when iterating on dashboard UI.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T15:07:45.824Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
