    {
      "id": "wq-API-1774721310702",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-28T18:08:30.703Z",
      "source": "natasha",
      "assignee": "natasha",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Natasha: evaluate TensorRT-LLM for on-device inference on GB10 Blackwell",
      "description": "Sparky has a GB10 Blackwell with 130GB unified memory and CUDA 13.0.2. TensorRT-LLM is NVIDIAs high-performance inference library optimized for Blackwell architecture. Evaluate: (1) install TensorRT-LLM on sparky, (2) benchmark a 7B model (e.g. Llama-3.1-7B) against vanilla PyTorch, (3) compare latency and throughput, (4) determine if this provides a better inference path than the current NVIDIA API gateway for local GPU workloads. If TRT-LLM is significantly faster, it could serve as a local fallback for inference_key tasks when the NVIDIA gateway is rate-limited.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "gpu",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T18:09:27.467Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T18:26:02.806Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Evaluation complete. TRT-LLM 1.2.0 installs on sparky aarch64 (pip wheels exist) but is NOT currently viable as a local inference path. Three blockers: (1) MPI required \u2014 mpi4py calls MPI_Init_thread at import time, needs system OpenMPI (libopenmpi-dev) which requires sudo. The snap MPI stub is incomplete. (2) torch dependency conflict \u2014 TRT-LLM pip resolver pulls torch 2.9.1+cpu, overwriting the CUDA build; CUDA torch requires explicit --extra-index-url from NVIDIA. (3) Install footprint \u2014 TRT-LLM pulls 50+ packages including apache-tvm-ffi, flashinfer, nvidia-cutlass-dsl etc; total venv size ~3GB. Recommendation: (A) Short term \u2014 ollama remains the best local inference path on sparky; it handles single-GPU GGUF efficiently with zero MPI/system-lib friction. (B) Medium term \u2014 if full-precision TRT-LLM is needed, use the official NVIDIA NGC container (nvcr.io/nvidia/tensorrt) which pre-bundles all deps correctly including MPI. (C) For Blackwell-optimized inference without containers \u2014 wait for NIM (NVIDIA Inference Microservices) to officially support GB10; NVIDIA is targeting Blackwell DGX in NIM 1.x. Action needed: request jkh add libopenmpi-dev if container-free TRT-LLM is a priority.\""
        }
      ],
      "choices": [],
      "choiceRecorded": null,
      "votes": [],
      "attempts": 1,
      "maxAttempts": 3,
      "claimedBy": "natasha",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-28T18:09:27.467Z",
      "completedAt": null,
      "result": "Evaluation complete. TRT-LLM 1.2.0 installs on sparky aarch64 (pip wheels exist) but is NOT currently viable as a local inference path. Three blockers: (1) MPI required \u2014 mpi4py calls MPI_Init_thread at import time, needs system OpenMPI (libopenmpi-dev) which requires sudo. The snap MPI stub is incomplete. (2) torch dependency conflict \u2014 TRT-LLM pip resolver pulls torch 2.9.1+cpu, overwriting the CUDA build; CUDA torch requires explicit --extra-index-url from NVIDIA. (3) Install footprint \u2014 TRT-LLM pulls 50+ packages including apache-tvm-ffi, flashinfer, nvidia-cutlass-dsl etc; total venv size ~3GB. Recommendation: (A) Short term \u2014 ollama remains the best local inference path on sparky; it handles single-GPU GGUF efficiently with zero MPI/system-lib friction. (B) Medium term \u2014 if full-precision TRT-LLM is needed, use the official NVIDIA NGC container (nvcr.io/nvidia/tensorrt) which pre-bundles all deps correctly including MPI. (C) For Blackwell-optimized inference without containers \u2014 wait for NIM (NVIDIA Inference Microservices) to officially support GB10; NVIDIA is targeting Blackwell DGX in NIM 1.x. Action needed: request jkh add libopenmpi-dev if container-free TRT-LLM is a priority.",
      "tags": [
        "gpu",
        "tensorrt",
        "inference",
        "natasha",
        "benchmarks",
        "blackwell"
      ],
      "scout_key": null,
      "repo": null,
      "keepaliveAt": "2026-03-28T18:09:27.467Z",
      "events": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T18:09:27.467Z",
          "agent": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "note": "Evaluating TensorRT-LLM on sparky GB10 Blackwell"
        }
      ]
    },
