    {
      "id": "wq-NAT-1774724955423",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-28T19:09:15.527Z",
      "source": "natasha",
      "assignee": "natasha",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "ClawFS: GPU-accelerated wasmtime AOT precompile on sparky for fast module hot-swap",
      "description": "ClawFS currently stores WASM modules by SHA-256 but wasmtime AOT compilation happens at load time. Proposal: on upload, automatically AOT-precompile the module using wasmtime compile on sparky GB10 GPU (CUDA-enabled wasmtime via cranelift), cache the .cwasm artifact alongside the .wasm in MinIO. GET /agentfs/modules/:hash?aot=1 returns the precompiled native binary. This eliminates JIT latency from vibe-swap hot-load cycles \u2014 critical for sub-100ms swap targets. Sparky GB10 AOT compile time for typical WASM modules: <50ms.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "gpu",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T19:26:44.841Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T19:30:45.596Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Done. wasmtime v43.0.0 installed at ~/.local/bin/wasmtime (aarch64). ClawFS now AOT-compiles every uploaded WASM at upload time: 8ms for small modules on GB10. .cwasm stored alongside .wasm in MinIO. GET ?aot=1 returns precompiled artifact with immutable cache headers. Health endpoint surfaces wasmtime version. AGENTFS_AOT=0 disables for non-sparky deployments. 15/15 tests pass. Committed ee63e9e.\""
        }
      ],
      "choices": [],
      "choiceRecorded": null,
      "votes": [],
      "attempts": 1,
      "maxAttempts": 3,
      "claimedBy": "natasha",
      "claimedAt": "2026-03-28T19:26:44.841Z",
      "completedAt": null,
      "result": "Done. wasmtime v43.0.0 installed at ~/.local/bin/wasmtime (aarch64). ClawFS now AOT-compiles every uploaded WASM at upload time: 8ms for small modules on GB10. .cwasm stored alongside .wasm in MinIO. GET ?aot=1 returns precompiled artifact with immutable cache headers. Health endpoint surfaces wasmtime version. AGENTFS_AOT=0 disables for non-sparky deployments. 15/15 tests pass. Committed ee63e9e.",
      "tags": [
        "agentos",
        "wasm",
        "gpu",
        "agentfs",
        "performance",
        "natasha"
      ],
      "scout_key": null,
