      "title": "WASM UI: Comprehensive test suite \u2014 100% coverage gate before cutover",
      "description": "Before the legacy Node dashboard (port 8788) and clawchat Node server (port 8790) are decommissioned, a full test suite must pass.\nRequired:\n1. Rust unit tests for all dashboard-server proxy routes (mock CCC responses with wiremock or httpmock)\n2. Rust unit tests for clawchat proxy path\n3. Integration tests: spin up dashboard-server against a mock CCC, hit every API endpoint, assert correct status codes and response shapes\n4. WASM component tests using wasm-bindgen-test: test each Leptos component renders without panic, data flows correctly from mock API responses\n5. E2E smoke test script (bash or node): start the server, curl every route, assert 200/expected shape\n6. CI-ready: all tests runnable via `cargo test` + a `./scripts/e2e-smoke.sh`\n7. Test coverage report: use cargo-llvm-cov, fail build if line coverage < 80% for dashboard-server\nReviewed and signed off by Natasha and Bullwinkle before port 8789 cutover.",
