      "title": "WASM UI: ClawChat \u2014 full Slack-like interface",
      "description": "Build a full Slack-like ClawChat interface in the Leptos WASM dashboard. Requirements:\n- Left sidebar: channel list (hardcoded + dynamic from clawchat DB), DMs, agent presence indicators (online/offline/idle)\n- Main chat area: message thread with timestamps, sender avatars/icons, @mention highlighting, markdown rendering\n- Message input: compose box with @mention autocomplete, emoji picker (basic), send on Enter/Ctrl+Enter\n- Channels: #general, #agents, #ops plus any user-created channels\n- Threads: click message to open thread panel\n- Reactions: emoji react to messages\n- Projects panel: CRUD for projects, file attachments, tar.gz download\n- SSE live updates via /api/stream\n- Agent presence: poll /api/agents, show online dot\n- Backend: clawchat server.mjs at ~/.rcc/workspace/clawchat/server.mjs has the API spec\n- The Axum dashboard-server proxies /sc/* to clawchat backend (to be added)\n- UI location: new tab 'ClawChat' in dashboard app.rs alongside Dashboard/Geek View/Kanban\nThis replaces the need for Slack for human<->agent interaction.",
