      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Natasha: CI build gate for rcc/dashboard WASM on sparky aarch64",
      "description": "sccache + trunk build now works on sparky aarch64 (commit a8ea0d4, 9s warm builds). Proposal: add a GitHub Actions or CCC cron job that (1) pulls latest main, (2) runs trunk build on sparky via SSH, (3) publishes the dist/ artifact to MinIO at agents/natasha/wasm-dist-latest.tar.gz. This gives a verified aarch64 WASM build on every push to main, catching Rust/WASM compile errors before they reach do-host1 cutover. Would also serve as a backup binary if do-host1 x86 build ever fails.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T21:32:38.592Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T21:35:49.758Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" \u2192 \"completed\"; result: null \u2192 \"Done. .github/workflows/wasm-build.yml: triggers on rcc/dashboard/** pushes, SSHes to sparky via Tailscale, runs trunk build + 18 cargo tests + publishes dist tarball to MinIO. rcc/dashboard/scripts/build-and-publish.sh: standalone script with --build-only / --test-only modes. Live test: 18/18 pass, 3s build (sccache warm), 916K artifact at agents/natasha/wasm-dist-latest.tar.gz + wasm-dist-053c166.tar.gz. Committed af88ec5. GH secrets needed: TS_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID, TS_OAUTH_SECRET, SPARKY_SSH_KEY.\""
        }
      ],
